column15: Abstract: Annual Report Portal for Institutes In today‚Äôs academic environment, managing and consolidating departmental reports into a cohesive institutional annual report is a complex and time-intensive task. The proposed Annual Report Portal is a smart and innovative solution designed to streamline this process by providing a centralized platform for integrating, managing, and customizing reports from all departments.  The portal facilitates seamless collaboration by allowing departments to upload their reports in various formats (PDF, Excel, text), edit content, and customize layouts in real time. Role-based access ensures that admins, department heads, and reviewers can securely perform their respective tasks. The system offers advanced features such as data visualization dashboards, automated report generation, search and filter functionalities, and export options in multiple formats (PDF, Word, Excel).  Built using a modern tech stack comprising Django for backend, React.js for frontend, and PostgreSQL for data management, the platform ensures scalability, security, and ease of use. Additional features like notifications for deadlines, customizable templates, and visual summaries provide added efficiency and flexibility.  This solution empowers institutions to save time, improve accuracy, and enhance collaboration in creating their annual reports. By integrating technology into the reporting process, the platform fosters smarter education management, aligning with modern institutional needs.

column15: KARM is an Advanced Humanoid Robotic Assistant, an innovative idea designed to meet the needs and overcome the challenges addressed by the elderly and specially abled individuals. As the global population ages and the number of elderly individuals increases, there is a growing need for innovative solutions to support their independence and enhance their quality of life. Physically abled individuals and seniors often face challenges in performing daily activities, managing health conditions, and maintaining social connections. These challenges can lead to decreased independence, increased reliance on caregivers, and a diminished quality of life. KARM aspires to provide them with a sense of independence, comfort, and dignity by integrating advanced technologies such as advanced sensors, artificial intelligence capabilities to traverse challenging scenarios, recognize and respond to user needs, and provide personalized support. Its purpose is to improve the lives of elderly and specially abled individuals by providing them with a trusted companion that can assist with daily living tasks, promote social interaction, and enhance overall well-being.  Key Objectives : 1. Health Monitoring 2. Task Assistance 3. Emergency Response 4. Companionship and Social Engagement

column15: InvisiTouch : Empowering abilities through the invisible power of vision.  This innovative software solution empowers individuals with physical disabilities, especially those without hands, by enabling them to control computers through facial gestures. The system utilizes advanced computer vision, AI-driven machine learning, and augmented reality (AR) to recognize facial movements like eye blinks, head tilts, and eyebrow raises. The addition of an eye-blink mouse pointer allows for seamless interaction, offering an intuitive and hands-free computing experience.  Facial Detection Module:  Utilizes computer vision algorithms to detect and track the user's face in real time. Employs techniques like Haar cascades and deep learning models (e.g., CNNs) to accurately locate and recognize facial features. Compatible with common webcams or specialized cameras, ensuring accessibility for diverse hardware setups.  Eye Blink-Based Mouse Control Module:  Converts eye blink gestures into mouse control commands, allowing users to interact with the system through subtle eye movements. Single or double blinks are mapped to specific actions, such as left-clicking or right-clicking, enabling hands-free navigation and selection. Facilitates tasks like opening files, selecting text, and navigating websites, all through eye-blink gestures. Gesture Recognition and Mapping Module:  Classifies a wide range of facial gestures (e.g., frowning, smiling, eyebrow raising, mouth opening) and maps them to predefined control actions. Uses machine learning models (e.g., supervised learning, deep neural networks) to learn and classify gestures with high accuracy. Supports customizable gesture-action mappings, allowing users to define their unique control scheme.  Augmented Reality (AR) Interface Module:  Integrates AR technology to overlay interactive elements onto the user's environment, providing a more immersive control experience. Utilizes AR markers or object recognition to display virtual buttons or interfaces that the user can control via facial gestures. Allows for more intuitive and dynamic interactions with virtual objects or 3D environments, enhancing accessibility for various applications (e.g., gaming, education, virtual meetings).  Action Execution Module:  Converts recognized facial gestures and eye-blink actions into corresponding commands on the connected device, such as moving the cursor, clicking buttons, or typing. Seamlessly integrates with operating systems and third-party software, supporting accessibility tools like screen readers and virtual keyboards. Ensures real-time execution with minimal latency, providing a smooth user experience.  User Calibration and Adaptation Module:  Guides users through an initial calibration process to define personalized facial gestures and eye-blink actions. Continuously adapts to user-specific features and environmental changes (e.g., lighting, camera angle) to optimize accuracy and performance over time. Includes an easy-to-use interface for users to modify gestures or redefine mappings as needed.  Feedback Mechanism:  Provides visual or auditory feedback to confirm successful gesture recognition and action execution. Alerts users when an ambiguous gesture is detected, prompting corrective actions or offering alternative suggestions. Ensures users can confirm that their intended action has been accurately processed.  Performance Optimization Module:  Optimizes processing efficiency to ensure low latency and real-time gesture recognition, even with complex facial movements or large-scale interactions. Implements algorithmic optimizations and hardware acceleration (e.g., GPU processing) to handle intensive tasks like AR rendering and facial recognition. Minimizes delays in system response, enhancing the overall usability and user experience.  Safety and Privacy Module:  Ensures that all facial and eye movement data is processed locally on the device to preserve user privacy and security. Implements data encryption and user authentication to safeguard against unauthorized access or misuse of sensitive data. Guarantees that no personal data is transmitted to external servers, ensuring compliance with privacy regulations and standards.

column15: Tourists visiting popular attractions, such as temples or other significant sites, often face uncertainty regarding the waiting times to enter these locations. Long and unpredictable wait times can lead to frustration, wasted time, and a diminished experience for visitors. Without reliable information on crowd levels and expected waiting times, tourists struggle to plan their visits efficiently, which can result in overcrowding during peak hours or missed opportunities to explore other attractions.To address this issue, there is a need for a system that can provide accurate real-time waiting time estimates based on current crowd levels and offer predictions for future waiting times. This system would enable tourists to make informed decisions about when to visit, optimizing their schedules and enhancing their overall experience. Our project aims to develop a Waiting Time Prediction System for tourists visiting popular spots like temples and attractions. This system will provide accurate real-time waiting estimates based on current crowd levels, along with predictions for future visits to help tourists plan their trips efficiently.The Waiting Time Prediction System will analyze crowd data and other relevant factors to deliver precise and timely waiting time information. By offering both real-time updates and future predictions, the system will empower tourists to plan their visits more effectively, reducing the likelihood of long waits and contributing to a more enjoyable and efficient travel experience.

column13: PRPCEMS12. Cyber Security: Fraud Detection in E-commerce Transactions
column15: "Online fraud, including payment fraud and account takeovers, is a growing issue in e-commerce, leading to billions in financial losses and significant reputational damage. This solution proposes a machine learning-based fraud detection system that leverages technologies such as Anomaly Detection using Isolation Forest and One-Class SVM, Clustering techniques like K-Means and DBSCAN, and Supervised Learning models such as Random Forest, Gradient Boosting, and Support Vector Machines (SVM) toidentify suspicious activities in real- time. By analyzing transaction patterns, user behavior, and device information, the system flags potential fraud while minimizing false positives. Natural Language Processing (NLP) is also employed for analyzing textual data such as customer communications.  Adaptive learning through Reinforcement Learning and Neural Networks ensures that the system evolves with new fraud tactics, providing ongoing protection against emergingthreats. Designed to be easily integrated into existing e-commerce platforms via REST APIs and compatible with cloud- based environments like AWS and Azure, this scalable solution offers businesses a powerful tool for combating fraud and safeguarding customer trust."

column15: The project, we titled as "A Real-Time Medical Inventory and Healthcare Management System", seeks to address critical challenges in healthcare access and management. Advanced authentication methods (OTP, password, and fingerprint) ensure patient data security while enabling easy access to medical history and healthcare services and Hospital Management Portal. The app also integrates Google Maps for locating pharmacies and nearby healthcare facilities, ensuring 24/7 access to essential medicines. The project emphasizes streamlined communication between the front-end and back-end systems, delivering personalized and efficient services to improve the overall patient experience. column13: PRPCEMS8. Smart farming & Agriculture Development : Assured Contract Farming System for Stable Market Access
column15: Abstract FarmLink: A Blockchain-Based Assured Contract Farming Platform for Stable Market Access  In the evolving landscape of agriculture, farmers frequently encounter challenges related to unstable market access, unreliable buyers, and inadequate contract enforcement, which impede their ability to secure fair prices and sustainable livelihoods. Addressing these issues, FarmLink emerges as an innovative blockchain-based platform designed to establish assured contract farming relationships between farmers and credible buyers. By leveraging the inherent transparency, immutability, and security of blockchain technology, FarmLink ensures that all contract details are transparently recorded and immutable, thereby fostering trust and reducing the risk of default for both parties.  The platform features a comprehensive transaction dashboard that provides users with clear visibility into contract terms, payment assurances, and real-time updates on transaction statuses. Additionally, integrated buyer-seller chat functionality facilitates seamless communication, enabling prompt resolution of queries and fostering stronger business relationships. FarmLink‚Äôs smart contract mechanisms automate payment processes upon the fulfillment of agreed-upon conditions, ensuring timely and secure financial transactions for farmers.  By bridging the gap between farmers and reliable buyers, FarmLink not only stabilizes market access but also enhances the overall efficiency and reliability of the agricultural supply chain. The platform empowers farmers with greater control over their produce and pricing, while buyers benefit from a dependable and transparent sourcing process. Ultimately, FarmLink contributes to the economic resilience of farming communities, promotes sustainable agricultural practices, and supports the creation of a more equitable and robust agricultural market ecosystem.

column15: Basically, The purpose of our project is to control the  traffic issues in traffic signal areas.So, to overcome this traffic  signal issues we have an idea of fitting the IOT base speed  breakers(with shaft edges) and they are connected to the  real time traffic signal timing. column15: ### **Abstract: Interactive Educational Snake Game with Text-to-Speech and Multiplayer Modes**  **Project Title**:   **"EduSnake: Learn, Play, and Grow with an Interactive Snake Game"**  **Objective**:   EduSnake is an innovative, interactive, and educational version of the classic snake game designed to make learning engaging for kids. By incorporating **text-to-speech (TTS)** technology, customizable game modes, and a variety of features, the game helps children learn alphabets, numbers, and Roman numerals in a fun and immersive way.  **Key Features**:    1. **Text-to-Speech Integration**:      - Pronounces letters, numbers, or Roman numerals every time the snake eats an item.      - Provides positive reinforcement like ‚ÄúWell done!‚Äù or ‚ÄúKeep going!‚Äù to encourage kids.    2. **Educational Game Modes**:      - **Alphabet Mode**: Learn letters in alphabetical order.      - **Number Mode**: Learn numbers in ascending order.      - **Roman Numeral Mode**: Learn Roman numerals sequentially.    3. **Interactive Feedback and Hints**:      - Animations like confetti and sound effects upon correct consumption.      - Displays the next target (e.g., "Next: B") to guide players.    4. **Customizable Difficulty**:      - Slower speeds and simpler levels for younger kids.      - Advanced levels with obstacles and timers for older players.    5. **Rewards System**:      - Awards stars, badges, and unlockable content such as stickers, avatars, and themes.      - Progress is tracked, motivating kids to achieve milestones.    6. **Multiplayer and Co-op Modes**:      - Two players can collaborate or compete in collecting alphabets and numbers.      - Co-op challenges include solving puzzles and arranging letters or numbers together.    7. **Educational Quizzes and Fun Facts**:      - After eating items, kids can answer simple multiple-choice questions or learn fun facts (e.g., ‚ÄúA for Apple ‚Äì Apples are rich in vitamins!‚Äù).    8. **Themed Customization**:      - Kids can choose themes like animals, space, or underwater to personalize their experience.    9. **Additional Game Modes**:      - Puzzle mini-games that involve arranging items to form words or solve math equations, enhancing critical thinking skills.    **Impact**:   EduSnake bridges the gap between education and entertainment by leveraging gamification. It enhances cognitive and motor skills while making learning enjoyable and accessible. The project supports inclusivity by incorporating TTS for auditory learning and customization for various age groups.   *Target Audience:*  Kids aged 5-12 years. Parents and educators seeking engaging educational tools.  **Why Choose This Project**:   EduSnake aligns with the hackathon's goal of creating impactful, technology-driven solutions that engage and empower young learners. Its unique blend of education, interactivity, and creativity sets it apart as a tool for holistic growth in children.     **Future Scope**:   With the potential for scalability, EduSnake can integrate additional languages, subjects, and gamified learning modules, making it a versatile educational platform.   **Tagline**:   *‚ÄúLearn while you play, grow every day!‚Äù*

column15: Title: Interactive Science Lab - Enhancing Practical Education through Virtual Experiments Abstract: The current educational landscape often lacks practical, hands-on experiences, particularly in science education. Traditional classroom settings rely heavily on theoretical knowledge, which can limit students' understanding and retention of scientific concepts. To address this gap, we propose the development of an Interactive Science Lab, an innovative educational game that simulates a science laboratory environment. This platform allows students to conduct virtual experiments, explore scientific principles, and engage in interactive learning experiences.  The Interactive Science Lab aims to enhance practical education by providing a immersive and engaging learning environment. Key features include virtual experiments across various scientific disciplines, interactive elements such as drag-and-drop interfaces and animations, real-time feedback, and gamification elements to motivate and reward students. The platform will also include integrated lesson plans, quizzes, and a comprehensive glossary to support educational content.  By leveraging technology to create a virtual lab, we can overcome the limitations of traditional classroom settings and provide students with a more dynamic and interactive learning experience. The Interactive Science Lab will be accessible on both web browsers and mobile devices, ensuring that students can learn anytime, anywhere. Additionally, the platform will support multiple languages to reach a broader audience.  Through the implementation of the Interactive Science Lab, we aim to bridge the gap between theoretical and practical education, fostering a deeper understanding and appreciation of scientific concepts among students. This innovative approach has the potential to revolutionize science education and prepare students for future scientific endeavors.  Key Features: Virtual Experiments: Simulations for physics, chemistry, biology, and environmental science. Interactive Elements: Drag-and-drop interface, animations, and real-time feedback. Educational Content: Lesson plans, quizzes, and a comprehensive glossary. Gamification: Achievements, badges, leaderboards, and progress tracking. Collaboration Tools: Multiplayer mode and discussion forums. Accessibility: Web-based and mobile-based, offline mode.

column15: Our proposed web application is a Fitness Tracker designed to enhance user fitness routines by leveraging computer vision and real-time data analysis. This app uses a webcam or smartphone camera to monitor and evaluate exercises, providing users with feedback on the accuracy of their posture and counting the number of sets completed. By incorporating AI-driven pose detection, the app ensures effective workouts, minimizes injury risks, and helps users achieve their fitness goals. With a user-friendly interface, real-time posture analysis, and exercise tracking, this app offers a smart and engaging solution for fitness enthusiasts.

column15: Development of Audit script for Windows 11 and Linux OS as per CIS (Centre for Internet Security) bench mark  Background : Organisations across various industries face significant challenges in maintaining robust cyber security posture. Compliance with industry standard bench marks and guidelines, such as those provided by Center for Internet Security (CIS), is crucial for ensuring the security and integrity of their IT Infrastructure. However, manually auditing and ensuring adherence to these benchmarks and guidelines can be time- consuming, error prone, and resource intensive. Current practises often involve manual checks. To address these challenges, there is a critical need to develop automated auditing scripts tailored to CIS benchmarks. Detailed description: This software solution aimed to list out the control guidelines as per CIS benchmark for the following operating systems: - Windows (Reference www.cisecurity.org/benchmark/Microsoft_winodws_desktop) i. Windows 11 (Enterprise version) ii. Windows 11 (Standalone version) Linux (Reference:www.cisecurity.org/benchmark/red_hat_linux, www.cisecurity.org/benchmark/ubuntu_linux) i. Redhat Enterprise (8 and 9) ii. Ubuntu desktop (20.04 LTS, 22.04 LTS) iii. Ubuntu server (12.04LTS and 14.04 LTS) Preferable scripting language (PowerShell for Windows, bash/python for Linux). Expected solution: i. A user-friendly GUI based solution with capability to generate a report of findings. ii. Should be customizable as per organizational needs and scale to audit large and diverse IT environments effectively. iii. Scripts should be reliable and accurate in identifying the deviations from iv. best practices outlined in CIS benchmarks. v. Should facilitate easy update and maintenance to accommodate changes in benchmarks over time.

column13: PRPCEMS7. Agriculture, FoodTech & Rural Development : AI-Driven Crop Disease Prediction and Management System
column15: In modern agriculture, crop diseases pose a significant threat to productivity, causing economic losses and harming sustainable farming practices. Traditional disease detection methods are often slow, reactive, and resource-intensive, which exacerbates the impact of disease outbreaks. The unpredictability of disease dynamics, influenced by factors such as climate change, makes it difficult for farmers to take proactive measures. To address these challenges, the AI-Driven Crop Disease Prediction and Management System leverages Artificial Intelligence (AI), Machine Learning (ML), and Internet of Things (IoT) technologies to provide a data-driven, real-time solution for disease prediction and management.  This system utilizes historical data, weather conditions, and soil parameters to predict disease outbreaks before they occur. It integrates advanced image recognition and IoT sensors for real-time monitoring of crops, allowing farmers to identify early symptoms of diseases that are otherwise difficult to detect. By offering tailored disease management recommendations and promoting sustainable practices, such as reduced pesticide usage, the system aims to enhance crop productivity while minimizing environmental impact.  In addition to improving disease management, the system also supports precision agriculture by optimizing irrigation, pest control, and resource allocation. Through mobile and web interfaces, farmers can access personalized insights and actionable recommendations, empowering them to make informed decisions that increase yields and reduce losses. Overall, the system contributes to climate resilience, food security, and the development of sustainable farming practices.

column15: SMS spam detection project using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript:  Title SMS Spam Detector: A Web-Based Solution  Abstract This project presents a web-based SMS spam detection system using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. The system utilizes a machine learning algorithm implemented in JavaScript to classify SMS messages as spam or legitimate. Users can input SMS messages, and the system provides instant spam detection results. This project demonstrates a client-side solution for SMS spam detection, promoting user security and convenience.  Keywords SMS spam detection, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, machine learning, web development.

column13: PRPCEMS9. Blockchain & security: Fake social media accounts and their detection
column15: ChatGPT  You said: Fake social media accounts and their detection project abstract in short  ChatGPT said: ChatGPT Project Abstract: Fake Social Media Accounts and Their Detection  The proliferation of fake social media accounts poses significant challenges, including spreading misinformation, phishing, and identity theft. This project aims to develop an automated system to detect fake accounts by analyzing behavioral patterns, account metadata, and content authenticity. Using machine learning algorithms, the system will identify suspicious activities, such as irregular posting patterns, inconsistent profile information, and unnatural network connections. The project leverages techniques like natural language processing, user behavior analysis, and feature extraction to improve detection accuracy. The proposed solution enhances platform security, protects user data, and promotes trust in online interactions.

column10: Vidyalankar Institute of Technology
column13: PRPCEMS15.  Students Innovation(Software-Innovative, Creative and Impactful solutions)
column15: INCOIS provides fishery advisory services through Potential Fishing Zone (PFZ) advisories, benefiting fishermen by improving fishing efficiency and reducing fuel consumption. Current research aims to advance fisheries forecasting by developing species-specific advisories. This requires analyzing fish catch data and environmental variables to understand habitat suitability for commercially important species. However, the lack of a systematic mechanism to aggregate and store geo-referenced fish catch data from various sources leads to scattered, disorganized data, causing inefficiencies and confusion for scientists working on habitat suitability¬†models. We will make a comprehensive database and portal for managing georeferenced fish catch information, featuring modules for occurrence and abundance of species, and robust visualization tools like Tableau. This platform will enable scientific personnel to efficiently access, filter, and analyze data by species, location, time, and other comprehensive filters. Through Abundance portal, the user can understand the exact quantification of fishes whereas through Occurrence portal, the user gets the information about the fishes present in a particular area. The users will have an option to search the fish repository by location using a map. The location input by the admin will be mapped to the co-ordinates using Google Cloud Geospatial API.

column10: Shri Vile Parle Kelvani Mandal's Institute of Technology Dhule
column13: PRPCEMS10.  AI driven Smart Education: AI-based Personalized Career Guidance Platform
column15: Abstract: The ever-evolving landscape of education demands innovative solutions to meet the diverse needs of learners. This project presents an AI-driven smart education platform designed to provide personalized career guidance. Leveraging advanced AI technologies, the platform offers tailored recommendations and learning pathways based on individual preferences, skills, and career aspirations.  The system integrates adaptive learning models and dynamic persona-based interactions, simulating real-world and fictional mentors to engage users effectively. By analyzing user behavior, learning styles, and preferences in real-time, the platform delivers customized advice and resources to enhance decision-making and career planning. Key features include multiple-choice question (MCQ) generation for any topic, personalized tests, instant result analysis, and feedback to track progress and refine guidance.  With capabilities like retrieval-augmented generation, engagement profiling, and advanced response analytics, the platform ensures an interactive and intuitive user experience. This AI-powered career guidance solution aims to empower learners, streamline career exploration, and create a smarter, more responsive educational ecosystem.
